I first met @jakob5 during pre pandemic times where Jon was in charge of the fundraising arm Koa Anuenue for the athletic department over at Uh. I could see that his heart was into the betterment of the university as a whole and of coarse Uh Athletics. For me being a fan of Uh , growing up on the beautiful moments of island pride that the athletics provided over the years I felt the very same way. We came up with an idea of having In4mation connect with Uh thus creating some fresh excitement with a long lasting collaborative relationship. Alongside the marketing aspect we wanted to make sure that we gave part of our profit towards our drops directly to athletics. So with many years in the making we’re onto our first drop of many……. @toddshimabuku @fiks8 @in4mryan & I are super proud and honored for this moment we all been long working for. 

www.in4mation.co

It was at the beginning of @volcom ‘s rise and the inception / evolution of surfers doing things differently. For me we grew up just into the things we were into. From the young days of breaking to graffiti and that style that we all associated with at that time. The basics of hip hop was the norm then @wutangclan came along and changed the game ushering in the new. For us we felt like it was a movement more than the music. Inspired by the wu tang clan I drew the W in honor of my favorites of the time. This day @eric_baeseman and i paddled out to half point dodging sets and fighting current to link up on this one and only shot. Shortly after Volcom used this image as an add which made me ever proud for my ode to the Wu. 

Thank you @joey_sa_doy for the find!

With water being the world’s most precious commodity, it is unfortunate there are those who continue to manipulate it to their own favor. Created by Mother Nature, water should be for all to use to live. Hawai’i is battling its own crisis with contaminated water and major entities remain in cahoots with the State to funnel OUR resources for profit. Today is #worldwaterday. Please pass on the message and beautiful art created with / by  @punkyaloha

“There’s been a thriving mid century movement in Hawaii from the initial creatives like Alford Pries and Vladamir Ossipoff to now with the likes of @hawaii_modern and @handcutmodern (lamp pictured at the famed Palehua @ossipoffcabin & Mark in studio). For us we’re inspired from the world around us thus the the Tv Head short sleeve button up design.”

📷 of @ziggy_jo 

A cool 10 days with my eldest son Ziggy was one of realizing what Hawaii means to many of us. As we cruised around surfing the last South swell Ziggy was treated so well by everyone we came across. They truly made him feel welcome and looked out for. Then it hit me. Hawaii is a place where we look out for each other , it’s a place that many of our friends kids are treated like as if they are our own .This magic still thrives and is evident more and more. Im glad Ziggy felt the love as he is loved here.
